<Group labelreference="L2">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">? DEplot</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L3" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" size="16" layout="Normal"><Font size="16">The purpose of this worksheet is to look at the differences between various models of flows with circular stream and pathlines.  Such flows are called vortices, such as the one you can observe in your bathtub when you pull the plug.  It is an experimentally observed fact (mostly from sattelite altimetry) that the oceans are full of large vortices called eddies.  As computer models get to the point where these eddies become well resolved (some models do this now, but the ones used for things like climate forecasts do not), the study of vortices will increase in prominence.</Font></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L16">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">with(DEtools); with(plots);</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output>
<Text-field style="2D Output" layout="Maple Output"><Equation executable="false" style="2D Output"></Equation></Text-field>
</Output>
<Output>
<Text-field style="2D Output" layout="Maple Output"><Equation executable="false" style="2D Output"></Equation></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L4">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">setoptions(axesfont=[COURIER,20],titlefont=[COURIER,20]);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L17" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" size="16" layout="Normal"><Font size="16">The above just sets the font.  The stuff below is how one would use Maple to solve a small system of DEs.  I don't really use Maple to solve DEs in my own work, so the stuff below is pretty much cobbled together from the help pages (which are rather good on Maple).</Font></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L5">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">F1 := proc(N,t,X,XP)                   # First order system
   XP[1] := -X[2]/(X[1]*X[1]+X[2]*X[2]);
   XP[2] := X[1]/(X[1]*X[1]+X[2]*X[2]);
end proc;
DEplot(F1,[x(t),y(t)],t=0..20,number=2,[[x(0)=.5,y(0)=0],[x(0)=1,y(0)=0],
[x(0)=2,y(0)=0]],stepsize=.01,title=`Path lines Irrotational Vortex`,
color=[.3*y(t)*(x(t)-1),x(t)*(1-y(t)),.1],linecolor=[black,blue,red],arrows=MEDIUM,
method=rkf45,font=[COURIER,16],titlefont=[COURIER,16]);DEplot(F1,x(t),t=0..20,number=2,[[x(0)=0.5,y(0)=0],[x(0)=1,y(0)=0],
[x(0)=2,y(0)=0]],stepsize=.01,title=`x vs t Irrotational Vortex`,
linecolor=[black,blue,red],arrows=none,
method=rkf45,font=[COURIER,16],titlefont=[COURIER,16],labels=[&quot;t&quot;,&quot;x&quot;]); r:=sqrt(x*x+y*y); u1:=-y/(r*r); v1:=x/(r*r); vort1:=simplify(diff(v1,x)-diff(u1,y)); e11_1:=diff(u1,x); e12_1:=0.5*(diff(u1,y)+diff(v1,x)); e22_1:=diff(v1,y);visc_forcex:=diff(e11,x)+diff(e12,y);visc_forcey:=diff(e12,x)+diff(e22,y);</Text-field>
</Input>
